{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Hello HomeController!{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div class="container">
 
  <div class="bg-light p-5 rounded">
    <h1>Symfony 5 Authenticator</h1>
    <p class="lead">This is a skeleton project showcasing new Authenticator based security.</p>
    <p class="lead">Since support for Gaurd based authentication is deprecated since version 5.3 it is advised to move towards the new authenticator based security</p>
    <a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" href="https://symfony.com/doc/current/security/authenticator_manager.html" role="button">Check official docs &raquo;</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
 
  <div class="bg-light p-5 rounded">
    <h3>Features</h3>
    <ol>
    <li><p class="lead">New User Registration</p></li>
    <p> During the registration process</p>
    <ol>
      <li> New user is assigned ROLE_USER and ROLE_MEMBER roles</li>
      <li> Persist the User into the database  </li>
      <li> To avoid having the user to login again :-</li>
          <ol>
              <li> Authenticate the User using the new authenticator <code>src\Security\CustomLoginAuthenticator</code>  </li>
              <li> Redirect the user to the member dashboard </li>
          </ol>
    </ol>
     
    <li><p class="lead">Login</p> </li>
    <p> During the Login process</p>
    <ol>
      <li> <code>src\Security\SecurityController</code> handles the <code>/login /logout </code></li>
      <li> Once the login form is submitted our custom security authenticator kicks-in. It is 
      located under <code>src\Security\CustomLoginAuthenticator</code> which is extended from <code>AbstractLoginFormAuthenticator</code></li>
      <li><code> OnAuthenticationSuccess </code> in <code>src\Security\CustomLoginAuthenticator</code> the user is directed to member dashboard 
      </li>
    </ol>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
